    <selectionEntry id="d9f5-f02b-a124-5c49" name="Rapier Weapon Platform" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <rules>
        <rule id="cce9-bda5-c4eb-411a" name="Artillery" hidden="false">
          <description>The Rapier can only fire if at least one crewman is alive. When a battery of Rapiers is fired at, randomize any hits between the crew and the Rapiers by rolling a D6: 1-3 hits the crew, 4-6 hits the Rapier. Hits against the crew are resolved as normal. Rapiers count as vehicles with an armour value of 10. Any penetrating or glancing hits destroy them.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule id="981a-e132-c3ca-7f52" name="Rapier Battery" hidden="false">
          <description>Rapiers can move up to 6&quot; in the movement phase, but may not shoot if they move (they may turn in place and fire). Rapiers may not move in the assault phase; if their crew decide or are forced to move in the assault phase for any reason, then their Rapiers are abandoned and should be removed from play, though the crew may keep on fighting as normal. The Rapiers will also be abandoned if the crew ever fall back 7&quot; or more.
Rapiers treat difficult terrain in the same way as a bike; roll a d6 when they enter or move in difficult terrain; on a roll of 1 the Rapier is destroyed and removed from play. Again, the crew may keep on operating as normal without the weapon.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
