    <selectionEntry id="14ca-abd5-fa44-8f96" name="Robots" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
      <selectionEntryGroups>
        <selectionEntryGroup id="8e54-12ad-514c-9d31" name="Robots" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true">
          <constraints>
            <constraint field="selections" scope="parent" value="4.0" percentValue="false" shared="true" includeChildSelections="false" includeChildForces="false" id="a3d8-6247-93c0-5378" type="max"/>
            <constraint field="selections" scope="parent" value="1.0" percentValue="false" shared="true" includeChildSelections="false" includeChildForces="false" id="4811-3705-903a-202a" type="min"/>
          </constraints>
          <rules>
            <rule id="68cc-935c-9c70-bce6" name="Robots" hidden="false">
              <description>Robots are sturdy constructions akin to walkers, thus may fire all equipped weapons and always count as stationary when firing their weapons, and may assault even if firing heavy or rapid fire weapons.
While taken as a single unit and deployed together, the robots count as seperate units once the game begins.
While masterpieces of technology, robots have very rudimentary programming and must be guided in battle by a guildmaster, if the guildmaster is not in guiding range for whatever reason, the robots will fall back to their basic programming.
If a robot model begin its turn without a guildmaster within 6&quot;, they must react according to their programming (Offensive or Defensive).</description>
            </rule>
          </rules>
          <selectionEntries>
            <selectionEntry id="d4de-a07a-a88f-2a9a" name="Crusader" hidden="false" collective="false" import="true" type="upgrade">
              <profiles>
                <profile id="484c-2dc6-5fd4-e579" name="Crusader" hidden="false" typeId="1e16-2bd8-7cad-379b" typeName="Unit">
                  <characteristics>
                    <characteristic name="WS" typeId="c704-6128-f143-935a">6</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="BS" typeId="7928-3a9b-6080-ed95">2</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="S" typeId="df03-6292-d3f5-f778">5</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="T" typeId="e5f6-94c4-de8c-5fa8">8</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="W" typeId="4dc2-c603-0bc5-0561">3</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="I" typeId="eeda-4fb4-901e-b70d">6</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="A" typeId="abbf-0d11-fd86-d938">2(3)</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="Ld" typeId="f47e-b15a-8f58-703c">N/A</characteristic>
                    <characteristic name="Sv" typeId="b309-5233-122f-82bb">2+/6++</characteristic>
                  </characteristics>
                </profile>
              </profiles>
              <rules>
                <rule id="af95-2d27-1f1f-e01c" name="Assault Program" hidden="false">
                  <description>If not guided this model must designate the closest enemy unit as it&apos;s primary target, then move it&apos;s full distance towards it in the movement phase, advance using fleet of foot and then assault it (if able). </description>
                </rule>
              </rules>
              <infoLinks>
                <infoLink id="8ddc-6556-0c57-af93" name="Power Weapon" hidden="false" targetId="5774-7187-2616-dd8a" type="profile"/>
