  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="za84-af1e-096b-0f33" name="Dangerous Over Short Distances" hidden="false">
      <description>Due to their low mobility, Squats must roll 3d6 and choose the lowest two results when fleeing or performing sweeping advances.
In addition, Squats may choose to move using the Slow and Purposeful universal special rule instead of moving normally.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="zb31-e90f-dae3-6887" name="Exo-Armour" hidden="false">
      <description>A model with exo-armour has the Slow and Purposeful and True Grit universal special rules, a saving throw of 2+, an invulnerable save of 6+, its toughness increased by 1 and attacks increased by 1. Units equipped with exo-armor can emerge from hidden tunnels on the battlefield, so they can use the Deep Strike rules but only if the mission allows it. In addition, the troops with exo-armor that win a hand-to-hand combat cannot perform sweeping advances. Due to the bulk of the exo-armour, only the spacious land raiders may transport them and they count as 2 models for transporting.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="cddd-4e91-ca04-813d" name="Stubborn" hidden="false">
      <description>Squats are notoriously stubborn and are wont to abandon their entrenched positions easily. If a unit of Squats has not moved in their previous turn they gain the Fearless universal special rule.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="bac7-a948-28c5-47f5" name="Ancestral Foe" hidden="false">
      <description>The Squats have fought many long and bitter wars against the Orks and bear an enduring enmity against the whole greenskinned race. Squats have the Hated (Orks) universal special rule.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
